Preheat your #oven{} to 210°C. Pop the @cauliflower florets{300%g} and @sweet potato{200%g}(diced) on two separate #baking trays{}. Sprinkle the @ground cumin{1%tsp} over both of them.

Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Roast in your oven until browned and tender, about ~{18%minutes}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Halve the @lime{1/2}. Drain and rinse the @lentils{} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium high heat. Once hot, add the shallot and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the garlic and @Zanzibar style curry powder{1} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @vegetable stock powder{1} and @water{50%ml}, mix well then add the lentils. Season with salt and pepper, then bring to a simmer and cook for ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} to the lentils and handful at a time and stir until it has all wilted and is piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Once the cauliflower and sweet potato are cooked, add to the lentils and stir through with half the coriander and a squeeze of lime juice. Taste and add more salt and pepper if you like. Cut any remaining lime into wedges.

Divide the curry between #bowls{}, top with the remaining coriander and serve with any remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!

> This Spiced Lentil Curry & Cauliflower recipe is packed full of tasty vegetables - a delicious dinner to conveniently help with your five a day.